<div id="review_4026912969" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4026912969" />
    <a title="Kathleen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48502194-kathleen"><img alt="Kathleen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447215825p2/48502194.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4026912969?book_show_action=true">Jun 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathleen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathleen" href="/user/show/48502194-kathleen">Kathleen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48502194-kathleen?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48502194-kathleen?shelf=setting-california">setting-california</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48502194-kathleen?shelf=classic">classic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48502194-kathleen?shelf=noir">noir</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4026912969" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11712327022809045278"><i>“The voice has no lust. He never told me to rape or steal. He just tells me how it is if I want to survive. Survive like a man. When the voice speaks, I listen.”</i><br/><br/>This doesn’t feel the same as other crime noir I’ve read. It feels special, like literary noir. It has this fabulous dark atmosphere, the usual range of criminals, cops and danger at every turn. But there’s more.<br/><br/>What I liked best was the introspective character of Easy Rawlins. I can understand why Walter Mosley has gotten so much mileag</span>
  <span id="freeText11712327022809045278" style="display:none"><i>“The voice has no lust. He never told me to rape or steal. He just tells me how it is if I want to survive. Survive like a man. When the voice speaks, I listen.”</i><br /><br />This doesn’t feel the same as other crime noir I’ve read. It feels special, like literary noir. It has this fabulous dark atmosphere, the usual range of criminals, cops and danger at every turn. But there’s more.<br /><br />What I liked best was the introspective character of Easy Rawlins. I can understand why Walter Mosley has gotten so much mileage out of him. He’s complex and thoughtful and likeable but with an edge.<br /><br />The book starts like a character study, with Easy wanting something. He wants to keep his little house in Watts. It’s 1948, and he’s lost his job at the aircraft plant, so what is he going to do? Even before the action gets exciting, we want to know the answer to this question.<br /><br />Easy starts interesting--a WWII vet facing financial struggles and racism, and gets more and more interesting, as we learn about the inner voice that guides him, the friends he can and can’t count on, and his instincts that lead him in and out of trouble. <br /><br />So this was a great train-wreck noir mystery, with life and death and sex and intrigue. But it’s the character of Easy Rawlins that’s making me look forward to the next in the series. I can’t wait to find out what he gets into next, and how he uses his friendships and his experiences and his smarts to get out of it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11712327022809045278" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

